- Matsenko,S Sitges 2015 Now the energetic} 16. Ng3 $1 $146 Bxc4 17. Nf5 {
, followed by Rf3-g3 offering White a stunning attack.}) 13. Ng3 fxe4 14. Nxe4
$36 {Black's king felt very exposed in view of ..Ng5 in Grischuk, A - Karjakin,
S Moscow 2023}) (10... Ba6 $5 {is a standard approach, but nobody tried it yet.
} 11. Bg5 h6 12. Bh4 e5 {Black has to stabilize the situation in the centre -
otherwise, e4-e5 will be very powerful.} ({Too risky is} 12... g5 13. Bg3 Nh5
14. h4 $1 {White has decent attacking prospects.}) 13. d5 Na5 {The Pc4 is
about to fall, but it isn't a big deal.} 14. f3 Bxc4 (14... Nxc4 {is
antu-intuitive, but possible. White has many interesting options, such as} 15.
Qa4 $5 Ne3 {The only move!} 16. Bxf6 {Stepping away of further fork with ...
Nxg2+} Qxf6 17. Qxa6 Nxg2+ 18. Kd2 Qxf3 19. Rhg1 {Black got 3 pawns for a
piece, but his task seems tougher from a practical point of view: White's king
