) 15. Ng3 $1 {A brave sacrifice! Black has to accept a piece because otherwise
White will develop a free attack by means of Nf5,g2-g4, e.t.c} g5 16. Bxg5 hxg5
17. Nf5 {A spectacular position! Black is a piece up, but White's attack fully
compensates it! Moreover, it is easy for Black to go astray and get
checkmated! for instance,} Nh7 {A natural attempt to organize defence with ...
f7-f6, Rf7, e.t.c} ({Safer is} 17... Nh5 $5 18. h4 g4 19. fxg4 Ng7 {, but also
then White's chances are by no means worse.}) 18. Bxc4 Nxc4 19. h4 f6 20. Qe2
Na5 $2 {This timid move loses on a spot:} 21. f4 $1 Qe8 22. hxg5 fxg5 23. fxg5
