is ..Nf5, and then g2-g4, Rb2-h2,increasing pressure on h7} Ng6 (15... f5 $2
16. exf5 Nxf5 17. Ne4 {, followed by g2-g4 is just crushing because Black
cannot do with the upcoming attack on the h-file.}) 16. Nf5 Nf4 17. g3 Nxd3+ 18.
Qxd3 {White has a powerful initiative, while Black's extra pawn doesn't really
tell.}) 14. exf5 Nxf5 15. Ne4 $1 {It is essential to keep knights on the
board. Black has to do both with ..Ng5 and Bg5.} Nf6 16. Bg5 $14 {The pin is
highly annoying. White's main idea is opening the f-file with f3-f4, and then
his bishop pair should tell.}) (9... Ba6 $6 {is consistent, but faulty. White
is allowed to} 10. e5 Ne8 11. Nf3 {The knight is much more active than on e2.}
f5 12. d5 {The most aggressive choice.} Na5 13. d6 $1 {Black is almost
squeezing into his camp.} Bxc4 14. Bxc4 Nxc4 15. Qe2 Na5 {This was Petkov,M -
Dardha, D Vrnjacka Banja 2023 Black is up a pawn, but almost all his pieces are
