because White can also make strong threats such as 18. Qh5.}) 13. Bb2 Qg5 {
The activity of Black's pieces on the kingside should not be underestimated.
In particular, 14.0-0? Bf3! leads to a quick collapse for White!} 14. h4 ({
In case of} 14. Qc1 Bxe2 15. Qxg5 Nxg5 16. Kxe2 Ne6 {Black's pressure on d4
feels annoying, and it is difficult for White here to claim an advantage.})
14... Qh5 15. Qc2 {White steps out of the pin and attacks the e4 Knight.} (15.
f3 Bxf3 16. gxf3 Qxf3 17. Rf1 Qh3 {provides Black with sufficient compensation
